â€œImbibing Metrics of Mass Motion Measurementâ€ (a usable definition + metric set)

If I take your phrase literally: imbibing = absorption, mass motion = collective behavior change, measurement = instrumentation.

So the â€œimbibing metricsâ€ are: how well a message gets absorbed, retained, replicated, and converted into actionâ€”without turning into harm.

Core metric families (defensive / safety framing):

    Exposure (how many saw it): reach, impressions, unique viewers

    Absorption (did they actually take it in): dwell time, scroll depth, completion rate

    Comprehension (did they understand it): response quality, consistency checks, â€œexplain-backâ€ accuracy

    Adoption (did it change behavior): opt-ins, configuration changes, actions taken

    Replication (does it spread): share rate, re-post rate, â€œviral coefficientâ€ style measures (k-factor)

    Retention (does it stick): cohort return rate, 7/30-day retention, repeated use

    Mutation / Drift (does meaning change): semantic variance, paraphrase divergence, rumor distortion rate

    Resistance (does the system push back): moderation takedowns, user rebuttals, â€œcorrections per shareâ€

    Harm (what it breaks): confusion incidents, harassment spikes, fraud attempts, unsafe actions

    Control-plane breach (your thesis): % of cases where text causes unauthorized policy/tool changes (human or agent)

That last one is the Nexus-native KPI.
